2026-04-28T08:10Z claude created

--- body ---
## Context

User-observed pain point on 2026-04-28: a live `uv run maiba scan
tests/fixtures/ArchiveCCS.ris` (no `--apply`, dry-run) takes ~2–4 minutes
on the 223-record corpus. Two reasons:

1. **No progress feedback.** The CLI prints nothing until the entire scan
   finishes. The user has no signal that work is happening or how far
   along it is.
2. **No HTTP cache.** Every invocation re-hits OpenAlex and Crossref for
   every record with a gap. Re-runs (which are common when iterating on
   gap rules or thresholds) pay full network cost every time.

ARCHITECTURE.md §2.3 explicitly anticipates this:
> Add HTTP response cache only when a run takes more than ~30 seconds
> end-to-end on `ArchiveCCS.ris`.

That threshold has been crossed. Time to add the cache. The architecture
also requires the cache be safe to `rm -rf` without breaking correctness.

## Actions

### Progress (pytest-style, one char per record)
No new dep. Per record, print one character to `sys.stderr` (flushed),
followed by a newline at the end.

| Char | Meaning |
|------|---------|
| `.`  | Skipped — record had no gaps |
| `0`  | Not fixed — resolver returned None or confidence below `apply_threshold` |
| `*`  | Fully fixed — every detected gap filled by the resolver |
| `+`  | Partially fixed — at least one gap filled, at least one still open |

1. In `src/maiba/pipeline.py`, after the per-record decision in `run()`,
   call `_emit_progress(char)` which writes to `sys.stderr` and flushes.
2. After the loop, write `"\n"` to stderr so the next CLI line starts clean.
3. Suppress when `sys.stderr` is not a TTY (so logs and CI stay clean):
   `if not sys.stderr.isatty(): return`.
4. Add a `--quiet` flag to `maiba scan` that suppresses the progress glyphs
   even on a TTY. (For when stdout is redirected but stderr stays open.)

### HTTP cache (deletable, zero-state-compatible)
3. Add `hishel>=0.0.30` to runtime deps. (HTTP-spec-compliant cache for
   httpx; respects upstream `Cache-Control` headers; handles ETags.)
4. In `src/maiba/resolvers/openalex.py` and `crossref.py`, replace
   `httpx.Client(...)` with `hishel.CacheClient(...)` configured with a
   filesystem storage backend at a path from `Config`.
5. Extend `config/maiba.yaml` `http` section:
   ```yaml
   http:
     timeout_s: 10
     ...
     cache_dir: ~/.cache/maiba/http     # safe to rm -rf
     cache_ttl_s: 2592000               # 30 days; resolver responses are stable
   ```
6. Extend `Config.HttpConfig` model in `src/maiba/config.py` to include
   `cache_dir: str` and `cache_ttl_s: int`.
7. Expand `~` and create the cache dir on first use.

### CLI flags
8. Add `--no-cache` to `maiba scan`. When set, bypass cache (still
   makes network calls but doesn't read or write the store). For
   debugging fresh upstream responses.
9. Add `--clear-cache` as a separate verb: `maiba clear-cache` removes
   `cache_dir`. (Pure convenience; equivalent to `rm -rf <cache_dir>`.)

## Test (TDD red step)

```python
# tests/test_cache.py
import respx
from httpx import Response
from pathlib import Path
from maiba.config import load_config
from maiba.resolvers.openalex import OpenAlexResolver
from maiba.model import Item

@respx.mock
def test_resolver_uses_cache_on_second_call(tmp_path):
    cfg = load_config("config/maiba.yaml")
    cfg.http.cache_dir = str(tmp_path / "cache")

    route = respx.get(url__regex=r".*api\.openalex\.org/works/doi:.*").mock(
        return_value=Response(200, json={
            "title": "X", "publication_year": 2020, "authorships": [],
            "doi": "https://doi.org/10.1/x"
        })
    )
    resolver = OpenAlexResolver(cfg)
    item = Item(TY="JOUR", TI="X", DO="10.1/x")

    resolver.resolve(item)
    resolver.resolve(item)

    assert route.call_count == 1, "second call should be served from cache"
```

```python
# tests/test_progress.py
import sys
import respx
from pathlib import Path
from maiba.pipeline import run
from maiba.config import load_config

@respx.mock
def test_progress_glyph_per_record(monkeypatch, tmp_path, capsys):
    """One char per record, in order, on stderr; ends with newline."""
    monkeypatch.setattr(sys.stderr, "isatty", lambda: True)
    cfg = load_config("config/maiba.yaml")
    # Use a small fixture for determinism — good.ris (3 records).
    run(input=Path("tests/fixtures/good.ris"), output=tmp_path / "out.ris",
        cfg=cfg, apply=False)
    err = capsys.readouterr().err
    glyphs = err.rstrip("\n")
    assert len(glyphs) == 3
    assert all(c in ".0*+" for c in glyphs)
    assert err.endswith("\n")
```

A second integration test re-runs the existing
`test_end_to_end_on_archiveccs_subset` with cache enabled and asserts
the second run makes zero network calls.

## Exit criteria

- `make test` green: cache test confirms second call hits cache, not network.
- `uv run maiba scan tests/fixtures/ArchiveCCS.ris` (live, dry-run) prints
  one glyph per record on stderr (`.`, `0`, `*`, `+`), ending with newline.
- Re-running the same command immediately is at least 5× faster (cache hit).
- `rm -rf ~/.cache/maiba/http` between runs restores full network behavior
  without breaking correctness.
- `--no-cache` flag bypasses the cache.
- ARCHITECTURE.md §9 gets an entry: "2026-04-28 — HTTP cache added (hishel)".
